>>24272135
I used to think Endtown was legit brilliant. It's a weird comic, but it makes all its weird parts just work together. I think representing the post-apocalyptic wasteland as a featureless white plain was a great idea. He often introduced characters whose personalities were informed by their history, and their response to the apocalypse. It had this toon look, but somehow made it work with its insanely bleak setting, by embracing the internal logic of it.

The first sign of things going wrong was with the lizard city, Specifically, he changed the design of the lizards overnight, and for the worse. Then he introduced the braindead lizard girl. She stands in massive contrast with every other character, because she has virtually no history, and she's ridiculously upbeat because she's quite literally too stupid to grasp how fucked the world is. She's all quirk, all the time, and it's grating.

But then he started character assassinating Holly. That was already insufferable, but then came the flashback. Usually Aaron did flashbacks pretty well. They all went back to the personalities of the characters involved, and explained why they were the way they were. Those characters were also always present for their own flashbacks, commenting on things as they went. This worked. The Holly flashback was the longest one yet, taking up a year of updates IRL. And this dude does three updates per week. But she isn't there for it. So it's two characters looking in on her past, one of whom doesn't even know her, or the world in general. And it's all to make it seem reasonable to write her out.

So you gain nothing from it. It's exposition for a character that's going to disappear. A total waste. And it also ended the entire arc that was going on with... nothing.

Yeah, I stopped reading after that. Haven't returned since.
